Done. Fresh-eyes notes are appended at the bottom of `src/blog/people/drafts/Jim-Carrey.md`.

**Reviewed:** the Jim Carrey Type 7 draft — a strong, well-structured piece with a great cold open and a genuinely smart refusal to resolve the mysticism cleanly.

**The two biggest issues I flagged:**

1. **The Truman Show is missing entirely** — and it's the single most on-thesis film of his career. A man discovers his whole life is a staged performance and has to walk out to become real. That's literally the article's thesis, played in 1998, fifteen years before "Jim Carrey is a character I played." The body skips straight from Ace Ventura to Man on the Moon, leaving the one movie the reader is waiting for on the table.

2. **The grief is named only in the abstract.** Section 5's "public loss and litigation he could not improvise his way out of" is gesturing at Cathriona White's 2015 death and the suits that followed — the most concrete real-world pain of the exact era the section is about, and the real test of whether the "stop running and feel it" turn is genuine or a bypass. The draft flinches from its own strongest evidence.

I also noted the "running/escape" motif is repeated enough that the template starts showing, and the $10M check lands three times. No body edits made, per the command.
